│ THOUGHT: The crash happens because we iterate over Arg's users/uses when Arg doesn't have a materialized use list (hasUseList() is false), which triggers an assertion in                │
│ Value::materialized_use_begin. To fix this safely, we can add a guard: if the argument lacks a use list, then there are no actual uses tracked, so the lifetime intrinsic can be         │
│ considered dead in this context. Otherwise, iterate Arg->users() and check they are all LifetimeIntrinsic.                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ applypatch << 'PATCH'                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ *** Begin Patch                                                                                                                                                                          │
